## My Final Verdict

Three carats is the most consequential decision point in the oval cluster. Here's where I land:

**If you want natural:** The G-VS2 entry at [$36,883](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29441823?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (ID: 29441823) is the only tier that makes financial sense. Anything above F-VS2 is prestige tax, not visible beauty. Budget $38,000–$40,000 all-in with a simple solitaire.

**If you want lab:** The D-IF IGI at [$7,285](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29847163?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is extraordinary value. Total ring budget under $9,000 for a 3ct oval. This is the 3ct Lab Reset in action — the biggest lab savings ratio in this entire series.

**If you're between 2.5ct and 3ct:** The $9,200 Half-Carat Tax is real. Consider a 2.8ct or 2.9ct oval — the visual difference is minimal but the savings are material. Blue Nile occasionally has GIA stones in that range below $33,000.

